{{italic title}}
'''''Button for Sleep''''' ({{lang-bg|Копче за сън}}) is a Bulgarian children's play, written by [[Valeri Petrov]] in 1978.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://liternet.bg/publish16/valeri_petrov/index.html|title=ВАЛЕРИ ПЕТРОВ|publisher=Liternet.bg|accessdate=18 May 2015|language=Bulgarian}}</ref> It is a musical with music by [[Georgi Genkov]]. Several notable productions of the play have been put on in Bulgarian, including at the Youth Theatre "Nikolay Binev" in Sofia under [[Ivan Urumov]], the "Patilan" Municipal Theatre under [[Anastasia Iankova]], and the "Ivan Dimov" Dramatic Theatre in [[Haskovo]] and Puppet Theatre in [[Sliven]], staged by [[Zlati Zlatev]].

