{{Orphan|date=October 2015}}
The '''Mramorac belts''' were [[Iron Age]] [[Mramorac style]] luxurious silver and gold belts used in ceremonial and religious aspects by the prominents of [[Triballi]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sgi.co.rs/html/003/00314.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-10-19 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090918163022/http://www.sgi.co.rs/html/003/00314.html |archivedate=2009-09-18 |df= }}</ref> a [[Thracian]] tribe then inhabiting the [[Pcinja District]] of southern [[Serbia]] and western [[Bulgaria]]. The belts are characterized by special patterns, including [[anthropomorphism|anthropomorphic]], Zoomorphic and Swastika symbolism.
The type is named after [[Mramorac]], a place in Serbia.
==Serbia== In 2004, the Serbian National Museum acquisited two silver belts.
*10 silver belts were found in [[Batinac]], dating to 5th century BC<ref name="reference-global.com">http://www.reference-global.com/doi/abs/10.1515/PZ.2007.003{{dead link|date=February 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> *2 gilded silver belts of Myriad motifs were found in Batinac, dating to 5th century BC<ref name="reference-global.com"/> *2 silver belts, found in Vinča, 5th century BC<ref>{{cite web |url=http://scindeks.nb.rs/article.aspx?artid=0436-11059643005V |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-10-19 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110826205731/http://scindeks.nb.rs/article.aspx?artid=0436-11059643005V |archivedate=2011-08-26 |df= }}</ref> *Silver belts, with Meander patterns, found at the Morava valley, Iron Age<ref>http://www.doiserbia.nb.rs/img/doi/0350-0241/2007/0350-02410757175S.pdf</ref>
==Republic of Macedonia== *Silver belts dating to 5th century BC were found on [[Trebeništa]] site, near [[Ohrid]], [[Republic of Macedonia|Macedonia]].
