{{Orphan|date=June 2016}} {{Infobox civilian attack |title= Rugova massacre |image= |caption= |location= [[Rugova (region)|Rugova]], [[Kosovo]] |target= [[Albanians]], | coordinates = {{coord|42.2513|N|20.210|E|source:wikidata|display=inline}} |date= 16 February, 1919 |time= |timezone= |type= Mass killing |fatalities=432{{Citation needed|reason=Reference missing|date=September 2017}} |injuries= |perps= [[Forces]] of the [[Kingdom of Yugoslavia]] |motive= }} The '''Rugova massacre''' was a series of killings of [[Albanians]] committed by the forces of the [[Kingdom of Serbs, Croats and Slovenes]] in the [[Rugova (region)|Rugova region]] on February 16, 1919.<ref>{{cite book|title=The Saturday Review of Politics, Literature, Science and Art|publisher=Chawton publishing Company, Limited|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=j_JAAQAAMAAJ&q=rugova+massacre+1919&dq=rugova+massacre+1919&hl=sv&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwifoMjIu47NAhVG7xQKHRsPBMQQ6AEIMjAD|language=en}}</ref> The soldiers burned women and children{{Citation needed|reason=Reference missing|date=September 2017}}, raped and massacred a total amount of 432 Albanians. The report was compiled for the [[Kosovo Committee]] in exile by two priests who handed it to the British Brigadier General George Fraser Philips, head of the British Military Control Commission in Albania and Montenegro, in [[Shkodër|Shkodra]]. The survivors fled into the [[Gjakova]] Highlands in Albania.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Haxhihasani|first1=Qemal|last2=Xhagolli|first2=Agron|last3=Shqipërisë)|first3=Instituti i Kulturës Popullore (Akademia e Shkencave e RPS të|title=Folklor kosovar|publisher=Akademia e Shkencave e RPS të Shqipërisë, Instituti i Kulturës Popullore|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=q3AhAAAAMAAJ&q=masakra+ne+rugove+1919&dq=masakra+ne+rugove+1919&hl=sv&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjy48rsu47NAhUJuRQKHTKNAIcQ6AEIGzAA|language=sq}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Statistics of the Rugova Massacre|url=http://www.albanianhistory.net/1919_statistics-rugova-massacre/index.htm|website=www.albanianhistory.net}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last1=Prifti|first1=Kristaq|title=The Truth on Kosova|publisher=Encyclopaedia Publishing House|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=YBq5AAAAIAAJ&q=rugova+massacre+1919&dq=rugova+massacre+1919&hl=sv&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwifoMjIu47NAhVG7xQKHRsPBMQQ6AEIVDAI|language=en}}</ref>
